cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a framework for proactive decision support based on automated planning in AI. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The framework aims to improve the decision-making experience of human decision makers in human-in-the-loop planning environments, which involves human-computer interaction and falls under the scope of cs.HC. The proposed framework also involves search-and-rescue examples in a fire-fighting domain, which involves robotics and falls under the scope of cs.RO. The framework generates and analyzes landmarks to aid decision making, which involves machine learning and falls under the scope of cs.SI. Finally, the framework supports naturalistic decision making, which involves cognitive science and falls under the scope of cs.LG.
